pyiidbi
-------

pyiidbi is an Ingres Python DBI driver, it allows Python to connect to the Ingres RDBMS.

It is pure Python code so requires no compilation and for this reason should be portable.

pyiidbi aims for high usability and DBI complience.

Status
------

This is an early beta, expect nothing, cursor[.execute|.fetchall|.description] should be working soon - check commit messages.

Requiers
--------

Python with ctypes module (recent Jython or Pypy, any Python since 2.2).
Ingres OpenAPI.

Licence
-------

Same as Ingres OpenAPI.
